                {4, 5, 6} };
System.out.println(arr[1][2]);
```

A student writes the following code to find the maximum value in a 2D array, but it does not examine all elements. Which change would fix the bug?

```java
int[][] data = { {3, 7, 2}, {9, 1, 5} };
int max = data[0][0];
for (int r = 0; r < data.length; r++) {
    for (int c = 0; c < data.length; c++) {
        if (data[r][c] > max) {
            max = data[r][c];
        }
    }
}
```

